               <p>I had a ruffled shirt of 
               <persName id="t17820515-32-person330">
                  Richard
                   Sanderson
               <interp inst="t17820515-32-person330" type="surname" value="Sanderson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17820515-32-person330" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17820515-32-person330" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's to wash; he said it cost a guinea and a half; it was the second time of its being washed. The prisoner washed for me. On missing an apron, I went and searched the prisoner's lodgings; I found the apron: I then charged her with the shirt; she denied having it. I afterwards traced this shirt to a Mr. Hill's, a pawnbroker's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17820515-32-person331">
                  ESTHER
                   THORNTON
               <interp inst="t17820515-32-person331" type="surname" value="THORNTON"></interp>
